// Pin the EXACT trigger of the old self-typing failure with minimal responds.
// HISTORY: R1/R3/R4 originally pinned "a gate that applies a CONCRETE recognizer to a hyp
// does NOT self-type" — the wall was param_apply's own body (a raw `param_walker f x` call,
// unwalkable: the walker cannot walk itself). RESOLVED 2026-07-01: param_apply is routed
// through the §7A policed token, so `param_apply T <hyp>` inside a checked body now runs the
// recognizer through the SANCTIONED native path (the H-rule verdict — no more information
// than the already-sanctioned neutral_type + tree_eq reads). All three flipped to Ok true.
open use "../kernel/prelude.disp"

// R0: constant gate — never touches `cases`. Self-types (Ok true).
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((gated_inductive_respond ({T, m, c} -> Ok false)) unit_witness) = Ok true

// R1: gate applies a CONCRETE recognizer (Nat) to the cases-hyp. Since the token routing,
// this SELF-TYPES: the walk completes with the H-rule verdict (Ok false -> Extend InvalidType).
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((gated_inductive_respond ({T, m, c} -> param_apply Nat c)) unit_witness) = Ok true

// R2: the SANCTIONED pattern — inductive_respond applies the NEUTRAL motive to self via
// apply_policed. Self-types (Ok true) — this is Unit's/Ord's respond (metashape.test).
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape (inductive_respond unit_witness) = Ok true

// R3: concrete recognizer on the MOTIVE-hyp m (not cases). Also walkable now.
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((gated_inductive_respond ({T, m, c} -> param_apply Bool m)) unit_witness) = Ok true

// R4: concrete recognizer on the cases-hyp, result DISCARDED (both arms Ok false). The old
// failure here proved the wall was the walker rejecting the redex `Nat c` STRUCTURALLY,
// not the value it produced; the token removes exactly that structural rejection.
test param_apply ProjectingRespondShape ((gated_inductive_respond ({T, m, c} -> match (param_apply Nat c) { Ok v => Ok false; Err _ => Ok false })) unit_witness) = Ok true
